recordedBy: Andrew Salywon; Neil Snow & Martin de la Cruz
locality: Parque Nacional Los Haitises, Prov. Hato Mayor, Mpio. Sabana de la Mar, Boca del Infierno, en un cayo a 200 m de Boca del Infierno.
occurrenceRemarks: Few stemmed shrub ca. 3 m long growing  directly out of vertical limestone cliff overhanging the ocean. Probably exposed to sea spray. This species was only observed growing along the open ocean facing edge of forest. Petals white falling easily on contact.  Bark smooth, bronze-gray. SEMARN permit #010304
name: Mosiera cuspidata (Alain) Salywon

recordedBy: Andrew Salywon; Neil Snow & Martin de la Cruz
locality: Parque Ncaional Los Haitises, Prov. Hato Mayor; Municpio Sabana de la Mar, Boca del Infierno, en un Cayo a 200 m de Boca del Infierno
occurrenceRemarks: Small tree or few stemmed shrub ca. 2-4 m long growing directly out of vertical limestone cliffs, with stems overhanging the ocean. Probably exposed to sea spray. Only observed growing near the ocean at edge of forest or singularly on barren rock. Petals white, falling easly. Immature fruits green.
name: Mosiera cuspidata (Alain) Salywon
